Really disappointed in this location. Ordered a sandwich for delivery, explicitly requesting extra Dijon mustard, amongst other “extra freebies.” When it arrived, there was no Dijon. Simple mistake. I called and requested a remake. After passing around the phone three times and denying they even processed my order, the staffer miraculously found my order and proceeded to explain to me the meaning of “EZ” and “Extra”. She even asked the person who made the sandwich who stated she honored the special requests. When I asked how “extra Dijon” results in no Dijon whatsoever, she finally agreed to send a new sandwich. The new sandwich was correct. The delivery was fast and the courier was friendly and apologetic. It shouldn’t be this difficult to get a correct sandwich.

First let me start by saying I love jimmy johns. I always order the #9... sooooooo good..🤤... anyways was staying at the Eaton DC hotel on 2/29/20.. I placed an order with this location and this is my first time ever having them deliver food usually I go in and get my sandwich but anyways I ordered delivery I decided to go have a smoke while I was waiting..I was only outside a hot minute no less than 5 minutes because it was freezing cold.. but when I came back in the lobby the young man from jj’s was already sitting there and had called my phone about 3 times which I didn’t hear ringing.. but I was amazed and shocked by how fast the service was...jimmy John ain’t playing no games..lol

I wanted Avocado on a sandwich. JJs has a big selection of cold cuts but also has a Veggy, cheese tomatoes etc. I asked for addition italian sausage. I ordered an 8 inch and it was ready in 2 min. You can eat there but it's more a take out place. The bread role was plain and uninteresting. There was little avocado and it was a bit dry. No dressing. The price was $9 plus some $2 plus for the extra meat. Making an upscale price to say Bluestone coffee shop. Bluestone is considered expensive but it's Avocado mash with a poached egg is almost worth the price. Or salmon and avocado. JJs sandwich didn't satisfy. Probably the Italian cold cuts would have been a better choice. Service is fast. Place is clean it's on a busy corner. It's actually partly below ground. But windows above ground. It means you have about 10 steps down to enter.  Making wheel chair entrance complicated. Busy street if you park be quick. If your on a bicycle easy parking on side walk.  There is a CVS across the street. JJs also delivers

This place is a no-frills sub shop - says so in its description.  That being said, it's fast and tasty.  Their business is about volume, not customization - if you want spinach, toasted wheat bread or hot peppers, go to Subway.  They have about 8 styles/combos in 2 sizes on 1 white sub (they do have a thick wheat bread slice option, which is nice but not a sub) - you order by number and it's produced in minutes by a busy line.  ...And you're off.
